id: pm-uxkf
title: "GH-578: pm context summary.blocked and pm list-blocked count status-only, disagreeing with edge-aware pm next"
description: "GH-489/pm-l0bu made pm next edge-aware (items with open blocked_by deps count as blocked), but the two other read surfaces agents use still count ONLY status:\"blocked\": pm context (ctx) summary.blocked reports 0 at every depth, and pm list-blocked reports count:0, while pm next's blocked companion lists the same items with open_blocker_count. Since auto-unblock (GH-267) makes status=blocked rare, these counters are effectively dead fields — an orchestrator reading blocked:0 concludes everything is dispatchable while pm next disagrees. Fix = adopt ONE shared blocked-semantics helper (the pm next edge-aware definition) across context summary + list-blocked, or report both dimensions explicitly (blocked_status + blocked_by_dependencies) so the surfaces can never silently disagree. Fix in the shared status-derivation layer, not per-surface — pm-pfqi (list-* consolidation) and pm-kcs4 (context-noun consolidation) will inherit whichever semantics ship here, so land the shared helper first or with them."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[2]: agent-ux,consistency
created_at: "2026-07-17T10:06:57.292Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T10:10:38.866Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: pm context summary.blocked counts dependency-blocked items identically to pm next's blocked companion at every depth; pm list-blocked returns the same set; a parity spec asserts next/context/list-blocked agree on a workspace with edge-blocked (status open) and status-blocked items; docs state the single definition of blocked
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
